{
  "texts": [
    "The three twitter datasets (HCR, HPV, and Mask) are still challenging for the LLMs models, despite the improved performance over the baseline, VADER.",
    "Out of the six tools/LLMs evaluated, SiEBERT performed the best on three out of five datasets, suggesting that LLMs fine-tuned on large scale datasets can indeed generalize to new datasets, though their applicability to healthrelated social media data such as HPV and Mask is still limited.",
    "Weighted F1-scores of the models on the evaluation datasets.",
    "GPT-3.5-Turbo and FLAN-T5 are all zeroshot.",
    "BERT-based models are evaluated on held-out test sets."
  ]
}